2df028744e05292062706ccd2efaaeffb57d903cdfdb2a9716b0065f2825","event_uuid":"79e4279c-1615-4c81-b506-38e270c0e187","position":{"commit_sha":"5f9c3b2959bbc86b6d5d297ba8bea3f62e0483bf","position":"1784432977298073001-79e4279c-1615-4c81-b506-38e270c0e187"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"5eeaaf03d35227f15ab3cc20f21ca236a5f434ef6feff770ad89e6b489320fb2","event_uuid":"b6836367-9389-4c51-bda3-bf7e720bddb4","position":{"commit_sha":"f8e1d9df0ef22ac618c74bd62851e7e8df216704","position":"1784433391326723078-b6836367-9389-4c51-bda3-bf7e720bddb4"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416765389784001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## What\nAdd a 7th link relation `caused_by` (directional, non-blocking, non-cycle-inducing, Jira-unmapped) expressing \"this bug was caused by that ticket/change\", making bug provenance a first-class graph edge so \"source of bugs\" is a real traversal.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/schemas/common.schema.json` — add `caused_by` to the `relation` enum (canonical source).\n- `src/rebar/types.py` — regenerate the `Relation` Literal via `python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types`.\n- `src/rebar/graph/_links.py` — add `caused_by` to `CANONICAL_RELATIONS`.\n- `src/rebar/graph/_graph.py` — CRITICAL: line ~204 has a hardcoded tuple `(\"relates_to\",\"duplicates\",\"supersedes\",\"discovered_from\")` that returns False (non-blocking / non-cycle); `caused_by` MUST be added there or it falls to the else-branch and gets block-cycle semantics.\n- `src/rebar/graph/_hierarchy.py` — verify the non-blocking relation set includes `caused_by` (promotion applies only to `blocks`/`depends_on`).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/unlink.py` — update the `_USAGE` relation string (line ~28) and the directional-relations note (line ~30) to include `caused_by`.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/help/link.txt`, `src/rebar/_cli/help/overview.txt` — update the enumerated relation list (overview line ~16).\n- `src/rebar/_mcp_writes.py` — update the relation list in the MCP write surface.\n- `tests/golden/cli_help/*.out` — regenerate the ~8 golden CLI-help snapshots that enumerate the relation set (e.g. `link__help.out`, `__overview_help.out`, `__overview_dashhelp.out`).\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_graph.py`, `outbound_links.py` — leave `caused_by` intentionally Jira-unmapped (like `discovered_from`/`duplicates`/`supersedes`); add it to the unmapped set if that set is explicit.\n- `docs/ticket-model.md`, `docs/event-schema.md`, `docs/cli-reference.md` — document the relation.\n- `tests/unit/graph/test_caused_by_relation.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nFollow the `discovered_from` precedent exactly (directional, non-blocking, non-cycle, Jira-unmapped) so the change is purely additive: old LINK events and the reducer stay valid, no persisted data is rewritten, and back-out is simply ceasing to emit the value. The relation string is duplicated across several enforcement/help/golden sites (schema, generated types, `_links.py`, the block-cycle tuple in `_graph.py`, `unlink.py`, `overview.txt`, and the `tests/golden/cli_help/*.out` snapshots), so the edit set spans all of them; the single behavioral gotcha is `_graph.py`'s hardcoded non-blocking tuple, which must list `caused_by` or the relation wrongly gets blocking-cycle semantics. A dedicated relation (not reusing `discovered_from`, whose semantics are temporal not causal) is required so recovery-time and source-of-bugs can traverse causation directly.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (real temp store): `link a b caused_by` round-trips and appears in reduced links with relation `caused_by`; a `caused_by` edge is NOT treated as a blocking dependency and a `caused_by` two-cycle is allowed (asserts the `_graph.py` semantics); an old LINK event without the relation still reduces.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/graph/test_caused_by_relation.py` passes: `rebar link <a> <b> caused_by` exits 0 and `rebar show <a> --output json | jq -e '.links[]|select(.relation==\\\"caused_by\\\")'` matches.\n- [ ] the generated `Relation` literal in `src/rebar/types.py` includes `caused_by` and the schema enum has 7 values — unit test asserts membership.\n- [ ] `caused_by` is non-blocking and non-cycle-inducing: a unit test asserts a `caused_by` edge does not appear as a blocker in `ready`/graph traversal and a `caused_by` two-node cycle does not raise.\n- [ ] the golden CLI-help snapshots are regenerated and the `tests/golden/cli_help` suite passes with `caused_by` listed — asserted by the golden test going green.\n- [ ] a pre-existing LINK event with a legacy relation still reduces without error (back-compat) — unit test asserts unchanged reducer output for a fixture of old links.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/schemas/common.schema.json","reason":"relation enum"},{"path":"src/rebar/types.py","reason":"regen Relation literal"},{"path":"src/rebar/graph/_links.py","reason":"CANONICAL_RELATIONS"},{"path":"src/rebar/graph/_graph.py","reason":"non-blocking/non-cycle tuple"},{"path":"src/rebar/graph/_hierarchy.py","reason":"promotion set"},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/unlink.py","reason":"usage + directional note"},{"path":"src/rebar/_cli/help/link.txt","reason":"relation list"},{"path":"src/rebar/_cli/help/overview.txt","reason":"relation list"},{"path":"src/rebar/_mcp_writes.py","reason":"mcp relation list"},{"path":"tests/golden/cli_help/link__help.out","reason":"regenerate snapshot"},{"path":"tests/golden/cli_help/__overview_help.out","reason":"regenerate snapshot"},{"path":"docs/ticket-model.md","reason":"doc"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"2ca6e9f4-1ef3-478b-8518-5f5e27ce0868","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","schema"],"ticket_id":"0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d","ticket_type":"task","title":"Add caused_by as a 7th link relation (additive, discovered_from precedent)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["d64755ce-843a-4ac1-b985-7822dcbf784c","54b6b1e8-5ad4-46a6-9536-bc80574f7b96","1d548375-4aeb-4ad0-bf63-0ab456b73749","68b7be27-35b2-4a0e-bf90-813d0a219fd1","baf5c6d1-4b30-4026-8579-161410d55c72","2ca6e9f4-1ef3-478b-8518-5f5e27ce0868","79e4279c-1615-4c81-b506-38e270c0e187","b6836367-9389-4c51-bda3-bf7e720bddb4"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784433391326723079,"uuid":"d9141a8b-5b89-4b1a-903b-5446b34312f6"}